  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to assess the safety of autologous bone marrow derived cell transplant
      in chronic spinal cord injury patients. The hypothesis is that the availability of bone
      marrow derived mesenchymal stem cells at the sites of injury promote neuronal regeneration.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
